public void flush()
           throws GnException
Flushes the memory cache to the file storage and commits the changes. This call will result in IO . Use this method to ensure that everything written is commited to the file system. Note: This is an optional call as internally data is flushed when it exceed the cache size and when the object goes out of scope..
